What is Hydroxypropyl Starch Ether (HPS)?

Hydroxypropyl Starch Ether (HPS) is a modified starch derivative produced through the etherification of natural starch with propylene oxide. It is widely recognized for its outstanding thickening, water retention, stabilizing, and workability-enhancing properties. HPS is commonly supplied as a white, free-flowing powder that dissolves readily in cold water to form stable, viscous solutions.

Modern Hydroxypropyl Starch Ether products offer advanced functional properties including:

High Water Retention for improved cement hydration
Excellent Thickening Performance for enhanced viscosity control
Superior Workability Enhancement in dry-mix mortars and plasters
Stable Performance across wide pH and temperature ranges
Biodegradable and Non-toxic Composition supporting sustainable formulations
Excellent Compatibility with cement-based and gypsum-based construction materials
By improving water retention, adhesion, consistency, and crack resistance, Hydroxypropyl Starch Ether helps manufacturers produce high-performance construction materials while also supporting pharmaceutical, food, and personal care applications.

